    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-12-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-12-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="820"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d820">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.1216M/165.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-12-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 19, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Replying to Department’s telegram of December 17. In order to cover legal
                    formalities of the agreement President Diaz insists that <pb facs="0633" n="551"
                        xml:id="pg_551"/> the exchange of notes between the two Governments must
                    take place before any further action can be taken; also that a representative of
                    the company in whose name the work is to be done be designated to arrange the
                    details of free entry of materials with the Mexican department of finance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
